title: H.S. football: Gianni Failla’s three scores power Becton over Queen of Peace - Sports
text:
Senior running back Gianni Failla set a career high with three rushing touchdowns and Becton’s defense put in another strong performance in a 26-0 home victory over Queen of Peace in Thursday football action.
It’s the first shutout of the season for the Wildcats (3-1), who’ve allowed just 21 points through four games.
Failla got his first touchdown on Becton’s second possession of the game and then added another two touchdowns in the fourth quarter.
Becton’s other score came on a 12-yard scramble from quarterback Michael Bolwell.
